-- Belgium's De Persgroep to buy Mecom Group for 196 mln stg
-- By Aastha Agnihotri in Bangalore
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 02:40AM EDT
-- None



June 30 (Reuters) - European newspaper publisher Mecom Group Plc <MEC.L> said it had reached an agreement to sell itself to Belgium-based media group De Persgroep NV for 196 million pounds ($333.5 million).

Under the terms, Mecom shareholders will receive 155 pence in cash apiece, representing a premium of 35 percent to the stock's closing price on Friday.[ID:nRSd8585Ka]